---
title: "Home"
altTitle: "Hi, I'm Brian."
description: "Welcome to my home on the web."
priority: 1.0
withHead: true
pageClasses:
  - 'main'
  - 'index'
ember: true
layout: base
styles:
  - 'main'
---



<section class="intro">
  <div class="content">
    <header>
      <h2>Who am I?</h2>
    </header>
    <p>
      I am an Engineer at <a href="https://nest.com">Nest</a>/<a href="https://google.com">Google</a>. I have spent the past few years building and improving <a href="https://nest.com">nest.com</a>. Outside of work, I listen to music, play some instruments, do some camping, and more or less try to enjoy the life I lead.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="index-music">
  <div class="content">
    <header>
      <h2>What I've been listening to.</h2>
      <p>
        Music is a big deal to me. I am always looking for my next favorite album. Last.fm is a tool that I use to track my listening habits. Here are some of the albums that I have been listening to recently.
      </p>
    </header>
    <div id="ember-app">
    </div>
    <div class="center">
      <a itemprop="url" href="/thoughts/last-fm/"
         class="button">
        See more
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="thoughts">
  <div class="content">
    <header>
      <h2>I have thoughts. Here are some recent ones.</h2>
    </header>
  </div>
  <ul id="thoughts-list">
    <%
      const basePages = getChildPages('thoughts');
      const newestPages = basePages.sort((pageA, pageB) => {
        const dateA = new Date(pageA.data.date);
        const dateB = new Date(pageB.data.date);
        return (dateA < dateB) ? 1 : -1;
      });
      newestPages.slice(0,4).forEach(({ url, data: { date, description, title }}) => {
    %>
    <li itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
      <a itemprop="url" href="/<%- url %>">
        <h3 itemprop="name"><%- title %></h3>
        <figcaption itemprop="description">
          <%- description %>
        </figcaption>
        <date itemprop="datePublished" content="<%- date %>">
          <%- formattedDate(date) %>
        </date>
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Brian Anders"/>
        <meta itemprop="publisher" content="Brian Anders"/>
      </a>
    </li>
    <% }); %>
  </ul>
  <div class="content center">
    <a itemprop="url" href="/thoughts/"
        class="button">
      See more
    </a>
  </div>
</section>


